                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="notes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="note-t-1">
                            
    
<p>One of these studies is still extant: <hi xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" rend="italics">Man and a woman planting potatoes</hi> (<rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#ill_2503">F 129a / JH 727</rs>), after which the letter sketch of the same name was made (<rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#_144">F - / JH 728</rs>). The composition of the other one is now known only from <hi xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" rend="italics">Two women working in the fields </hi>(<rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#_145">F 1228 / JH 730</rs>), the sketch enclosed with <ref xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" target="let492.xml">letter 492</ref>.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
